|Example.Language=Spanish
|Example.Text=Un problema fundamental del BCE es que su conformación implicó la eliminación de dos variables de ajuste importantes: el mecanismo de tasas de interés de cada país y el del tipo de cambio, sin sustituirlos por nada; por lo que, cuando un país en lo individual enfrenta una crisis, no tiene forma de adaptarse a través de políticas monetarias o de tipo de cambio.
|Example.Gloss=a problem fundamental of.the EBC is that its configuration involved the elimination of two variables of adjustment important: the mechanism of rate of interest of each country and that of.the type of exchange, without replacing.them by nothing; by it that, when a country in it individual faces a crisis, not it.has way of adapting.itself through policies monetary or of type of exchange
|Example.English translation="A fundamental problem of the EBC is that its configuration involved the elimination of two important adjustment variables: the interest rate mechanism for each country and that of the exchange rate, without replacing them with anything; so that, when an individual country faces a crisis, it has no way of adapting itself via monetary policies or exchange rates."
